properties.areaDesc: Lake Superior from Upper Entrance to Portage Canal to Manitou Island MI 5NM off shore to the US/Canadian Border; Upper Entrance of Portage Canal to Eagle River MI; Eagle River to Manitou Island MI
properties.headline: Gale Warning issued January 20 at 9:44AM EST until January 21 at 4:00PM EST by NWS Marquette MI
properties.description:
* WHAT...West winds 20 to 30 kt with gusts up to 40 kt and waves
8 to 13 feet expected.

* WHERE...Upper Entrance of Portage Canal to Eagle River MI,
Eagle River to Manitou Island MI and Lake Superior from Upper
Entrance to Portage Canal to Manitou Island MI 5NM off shore
to the US/Canadian Border.

* WHEN...From 1 AM to 4 PM EST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous waves which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: GALE WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 1 AM TO 4 PM EST TUESDAY
